.TH SH 1 "16 June 2026" "OKU Foundation" "Usage Manual"
.SH NAME
.B sh
\(en the minimalist Oku command shell
.SH SYNOPSIS

\fBsh\fP
.RB [ -c
.IR command_string ]
.RB [ -v ]
.RI [ file ]

.SH DESCRIPTION

The
.B sh
utility is a minimalist command language interpreter that executes commands 
read from standard input, a specified string, or a script file. It serves as 
the primary interactive and scripting interface for the OKU ecosystem.

True to the OKU philosophy,
.B sh
is designed around absolute simplicity and architectural transparency. It 
dispenses with complex, heavy runtime abstractions, managing process execution, 
environment variables, and input/output pipelines via direct, raw system call 
interfaces. In alignment with tools like
.BR TAQBOL ,
it avoids unnecessary user-space runtime layers to ensure lightning-fast execution 
and completely predictable resource usage.

.SH OPTIONS

.IP \fB-c\fP\ \fIcommand_string\fP
Read and execute commands from the literal text provided in
.IR command_string ,
then exit.
.IP \fB-v\fP
Display the current version, build parameters, and OKU authorship credits, 
then exit successfully.

.SH OPERANDS

The following operand is supported:
.IP \fIfile\fP
The pathname of a text file containing commands to be executed sequentially. 
If no file or
.B -c
string is specified,
.B sh
enters interactive mode, reading from standard input.

.SH INTERNALS AND REDIRECTION

Like standard minimalist environments,
.B sh
supports essential process pipeline control mechanisms natively:
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
The vertical bar (\(oq|\(cq) operator routes the standard output of one process 
directly into the standard input of another.
.IP \(bu 3
File descriptors can be explicitly redirected via standard operators (\(oq<\(cq, 
\(oq>\(cq, and \(oq>>\(cq).
.RE

No massive scripting overhead or heavy internal variable caches are included; 
the focus remains entirely on directing and managing binary execution pipelines 
cleanly.

.SH ENVIRONMENT

.IP \fBPATH\fP
A colon-separated list of directories searched by
.B sh
to locate executable utility binaries.

